{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiskInjector"},{"type":"text","text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses Apple’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works","level":2},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Thread Safety","anchor":"Thread-Safety","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Process"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}]}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector"},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"DiskInjector","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","roleHeading":"Enumeration","symbolKind":"enum"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/daemonLa